notes: Wx 20:34 mostly clear, cloudy over mainland to north, 1/4 moon, SW wind 5 kn; 22:40 moon obscured by clouds, wind zero; 23:30 sky obscured by clouds; 23:46 wind up to 5-8 kn; 01:15 net billowing, wind 8-12 kn.First SCMU calling 20:42, tape on 20:55, 00:40-01:00 HRC checked 10-20 crevices but found nothing. General: The dive boat Vision was anchored on the south side with bright deck lights so we netted on the north side to reduce net illumination and generator noise. Some light from oil platforms Gilda, Grace, and Gail.

org: Calif. Institute of Env'l Studies (CIES)/Channel Islands National Park (CHIS)
notes: Approximate start time. ALH, DMM, REW, MWP. Land @ ~1945 set up net mid-spine on east side of Rat Rock. Using just CD player to start, net open ~2100. Standard net 38 mm, 2.6 x 9 m, 4 shelves. Wx wind NW 5-7 knots, vis 15+ miles, no moon, clear skies. Net shut down 2355 mesh too wide causing birds too much stress. See ALH notes.
